{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1388,"text":"When I die,"},{"time":3025,"text":"I would like for my body\nto be laid out to be eaten by animals."},{"time":9100,"text":"Having your body laid out to be eaten\nby animals is not for everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13835,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":14892,"text":"Maybe you have already had\nthe end-of-life talk with your family"},{"time":18869,"text":"and decided on,\nI don't know, cremation."},{"time":23013,"text":"And in the interest of full disclosure,"},{"time":25603,"text":"what I am proposing for my dead body\nis not strictly legal at the moment,"},{"time":31615,"text":"but it's not without precedent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34104,"text":"We've been laying out our dead\nfor all of human history;"},{"time":37716,"text":"it's call exposure burial."},{"time":40276,"text":"In fact, it's likely happening\nright now as we speak."},{"time":44864,"text":"In the mountainous regions of Tibet,"},{"time":47119,"text":"they practice \"sky burial,\""},{"time":49207,"text":"a ritual where the body is left\nto be consumed by vultures."},{"time":53725,"text":"In Mumbai, in India,\nthose who follow the Parsi religion"},{"time":58975,"text":"put their dead in structures\ncalled \"Towers of Silence.\""},{"time":63667,"text":"These are interesting cultural tidbits,"},{"time":66235,"text":"but they just haven't really been\nthat popular in the Western world --"},{"time":70707,"text":"they're not what you'd expect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73158,"text":"In America, our death traditions\nhave come to be chemical embalming,"},{"time":78212,"text":"followed by burial at your local cemetery,"},{"time":81617,"text":"or, more recently, cremation."},{"time":85023,"text":"I myself, am a recent vegetarian,"},{"time":88310,"text":"which means I spent the first\n30 years or so of my life"},{"time":91953,"text":"frantically inhaling animals --"},{"time":94184,"text":"as many as I could get my hands on."},{"time":96886,"text":"Why, when I die, should they not\nhave their turn with me?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":101490,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":103281,"text":"Am I not an animal?"},{"time":105185,"text":"Biologically speaking,\nare we not all, in this room, animals?"},{"time":111129,"text":"Accepting the fact that we are animals"},{"time":113805,"text":"has some potentially\nterrifying consequences."},{"time":117400,"text":"It means accepting\nthat we are doomed to decay and die,"},{"time":121452,"text":"just like any other creature on earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126256,"text":"For the last nine years,\nI've worked in the funeral industry,"},{"time":129894,"text":"first as a crematory operator,"},{"time":132049,"text":"then as a mortician"},{"time":133551,"text":"and most recently, as the owner\nof my own funeral home."},{"time":137342,"text":"And I have some good news:"},{"time":139098,"text":"if you're looking to avoid the whole\n\"doomed to decay and die\" thing:"},{"time":144694,"text":"you will have all the help\nin the world in that avoidance"},{"time":148934,"text":"from the funeral industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151820,"text":"It's a multi-billion-dollar industry,"},{"time":154009,"text":"and its economic model\nis based on the principle"},{"time":157017,"text":"of protection, sanitation\nand beautification of the corpse."},{"time":163610,"text":"Whether they mean to or not,"},{"time":165806,"text":"the funeral industry promotes\nthis idea of human exceptionalism."},{"time":170816,"text":"It doesn't matter what it takes,"},{"time":172482,"text":"how much it costs,"},{"time":173798,"text":"how bad it is for the environment,"},{"time":175780,"text":"we're going to do it\nbecause humans are worth it!"},{"time":179947,"text":"It ignores the fact"},{"time":181559,"text":"that death can be an emotionally messy\nand complex affair,"},{"time":186670,"text":"and that there is beauty in decay --"},{"time":189238,"text":"beauty in the natural return\nto the earth from whence we came."},{"time":195180,"text":"Now, I don't want you to get me wrong --"},{"time":197120,"text":"I absolutely understand\nthe importance of ritual,"},{"time":200131,"text":"especially when it comes\nto the people that we love."},{"time":203256,"text":"But we have to be able\nto create and practice this ritual"},{"time":206815,"text":"without harming the environment,"},{"time":208620,"text":"which is why we need new options."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212415,"text":"So let's return to the idea of protection,\nsanitation and beautification."},{"time":217479,"text":"We'll start with a dead body."},{"time":219852,"text":"The funeral industry\nwill protect your dead body"},{"time":222895,"text":"by offering to sell your family a casket\nmade of hardwood or metal"},{"time":227760,"text":"with a rubber sealant."},{"time":230263,"text":"At the cemetery, on the day of burial,\nthat casket will be lowered"},{"time":233858,"text":"into a large concrete or metal vault."},{"time":237753,"text":"We're wasting all of these resources --\nconcretes, metal, hardwoods --"},{"time":241701,"text":"hiding them in vast\nunderground fortresses."},{"time":246300,"text":"When you choose burial at the cemetery,"},{"time":248872,"text":"your dead body is not coming anywhere\nnear the dirt that surrounds it."},{"time":254750,"text":"Food for worms"},{"time":256328,"text":"you are not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258657,"text":"Next, the industry will sanitize\nyour body through embalming:"},{"time":263500,"text":"the chemical preservation of the dead."},{"time":266306,"text":"This procedure drains your blood"},{"time":268264,"text":"and replaces it with a toxic,\ncancer-causing formaldehyde."},{"time":273649,"text":"They say they do this\nfor the public health"},{"time":276016,"text":"because the dead body can be dangerous,"},{"time":278890,"text":"but the doctors in this room will tell you"},{"time":281413,"text":"that that claim would only apply"},{"time":284191,"text":"if the person had died of some wildly\ninfectious disease, like Ebola."},{"time":290021,"text":"Even human decomposition,\nwhich, let's be honest,"},{"time":293284,"text":"is a little stinky and unpleasant,"},{"time":296298,"text":"is perfectly safe."},{"time":298795,"text":"The bacteria that causes disease\nis not the same bacteria"},{"time":303327,"text":"that causes decomposition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306656,"text":"Finally, the industry\nwill beautify the corpse."},{"time":311181,"text":"They'll tell you that the natural\ndead body of your mother or father"},{"time":315094,"text":"is not good enough as it is."},{"time":317665,"text":"They'll put it in makeup."},{"time":319417,"text":"They'll put it in a suit."},{"time":321232,"text":"They'll inject dyes so the person\nlooks a little more alive --"},{"time":325195,"text":"just resting."},{"time":327672,"text":"Embalming is a cheat code,"},{"time":329962,"text":"providing the illusion that death\nand then decay are not the natural end"},{"time":334383,"text":"for all organic life on this planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338609,"text":"Now, if this system of beautification,\nsanitation, protection"},{"time":343651,"text":"doesn't appeal to you,"},{"time":345868,"text":"you are not alone."},{"time":347830,"text":"There is a whole wave of people --"},{"time":349830,"text":"funeral directors, designers,\nenvironmentalists --"},{"time":352818,"text":"trying to come up with a more\neco-friendly way of death."},{"time":357381,"text":"For these people, death is not necessarily"},{"time":359887,"text":"a pristine, makeup,\npowder-blue tuxedo kind of affair."},{"time":364746,"text":"There's no question"},{"time":366168,"text":"that our current methods of death\nare not particularly sustainable,"},{"time":370119,"text":"what with the waste of resources\nand our reliance on chemicals."},{"time":374498,"text":"Even cremation,"},{"time":375864,"text":"which is usually considered\nthe environmentally friendly option,"},{"time":379606,"text":"uses, per cremation,"},{"time":381868,"text":"the natural gas equivalent\nof a 500-mile car trip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387928,"text":"So where do we go from here?"},{"time":391368,"text":"Last summer, I was in the mountains\nof North Carolina,"},{"time":394744,"text":"hauling buckets of wood chips\nin the summer sun."},{"time":398741,"text":"I was at Western Carolina University\nat their \"Body Farm,\""},{"time":402954,"text":"more accurately called\na \"human decomposition facility.\""},{"time":407794,"text":"Bodies donated to science\nare brought here,"},{"time":410063,"text":"and their decay is studied\nto benefit the future of forensics."},{"time":414820,"text":"On this particular day,"},{"time":416132,"text":"there were 12 bodies laid out\nin various stages of decomposition."},{"time":420727,"text":"Some were skeletonized,"},{"time":423032,"text":"one was wearing purple pajamas,"},{"time":425428,"text":"one still had blonde facial hair visible."},{"time":429210,"text":"The forensic aspect is really fascinating,"},{"time":432143,"text":"but not actually why I was there."},{"time":434563,"text":"I was there because a colleague of mine\nnamed Katrina Spade"},{"time":437849,"text":"is attempting to create a system,\nnot of cremating the dead,"},{"time":442213,"text":"but composting the dead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444925,"text":"She calls the system \"Recomposition,\""},{"time":447467,"text":"and we've been doing it with cattle\nand other livestock for years."},{"time":451645,"text":"She imagines a facility"},{"time":453193,"text":"where the family could come\nand lay their dead loved one"},{"time":455843,"text":"in a nutrient-rich mixture that would,\nin four-to-six weeks,"},{"time":460298,"text":"reduce the body -- bones\nand all -- to soil."},{"time":464802,"text":"In those four-to-six weeks,"},{"time":466271,"text":"your molecules become other molecules;"},{"time":468753,"text":"you literally transform."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471706,"text":"How would this fit in\nwith the very recent desire"},{"time":474783,"text":"a lot of people seem to have"},{"time":476409,"text":"to be buried under a tree,"},{"time":477938,"text":"or to become a tree when they die?"},{"time":480710,"text":"In a traditional cremation,\nthe ashes that are left over --"},{"time":484264,"text":"inorganic bone fragments --"},{"time":486274,"text":"form a thick, chalky layer"},{"time":488549,"text":"that, unless distributed\nin the soil just right,"},{"time":491796,"text":"can actually hurt or kill the tree."},{"time":495552,"text":"But if you're recomposed,\nif you actually become the soil,"},{"time":498881,"text":"you can nourish the tree,"},{"time":500439,"text":"and become the post-mortem contributor\nyou've always wanted to be --"},{"time":504152,"text":"that you deserve to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506818,"text":"So that's one option\nfor the future of cremation."},{"time":510185,"text":"But what about the future of cemeteries?"},{"time":513112,"text":"There are a lot of people who think\nwe shouldn't even have cemeteries anymore"},{"time":517201,"text":"because we're running out of land."},{"time":519977,"text":"But what if we reframed it,"},{"time":522214,"text":"and the corpse wasn't the land's enemy,"},{"time":524843,"text":"but its potential savior?"},{"time":527805,"text":"I'm talking about conservation burial,"},{"time":530382,"text":"where large swaths of land\nare purchased by a land trust."},{"time":535274,"text":"The beauty of this is that once you plant\na few dead bodies in that land,"},{"time":540128,"text":"it can't be touched,\nit can't be developed on --"},{"time":543170,"text":"hence the term, \"conservation burial.\""},{"time":545992,"text":"It's the equivalent of chaining yourself\nto a tree post-mortem --"},{"time":549898,"text":"\"Hell no, I won't go!"},{"time":552386,"text":"No, really -- I can't.\nI'm decomposing under here.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":555455,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":556574,"text":"Any money that the family\ngives to the cemetery"},{"time":558919,"text":"would go back into protecting\nand managing the land."},{"time":563376,"text":"There are no headstones\nand no graves in the typical sense."},{"time":567799,"text":"The graves are scattered\nabout the property"},{"time":569970,"text":"under elegant mounds,"},{"time":571554,"text":"marked only by a rock\nor a small metal disk,"},{"time":575259,"text":"or sometimes only locatable by GPS."},{"time":578743,"text":"There's no embalming,"},{"time":580441,"text":"no heavy, metal caskets."},{"time":583300,"text":"My funeral home sells a few caskets"},{"time":585529,"text":"made out of things like\nwoven willow and bamboo,"},{"time":589305,"text":"but honestly, most of our families\njust choose a simple shroud."},{"time":593979,"text":"There are none of the big vaults\nthat most cemeteries require"},{"time":597843,"text":"just because it makes it easier\nfor them to landscape."},{"time":602101,"text":"Families can come here;\nthey can luxuriate in nature;"},{"time":605657,"text":"they can even plant a tree or a shrub,"},{"time":608358,"text":"though only native plants\nto the area are allowed."},{"time":612054,"text":"The dead then blend seamlessly\nin with the landscape."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616259,"text":"There's hope in conservation cemeteries."},{"time":620091,"text":"They offer dedicated green space\nin both urban and rural areas."},{"time":625747,"text":"They offer a chance to reintroduce\nnative plants and animals to a region."},{"time":630922,"text":"They offer public trails,"},{"time":632919,"text":"places for spiritual practice,"},{"time":634991,"text":"places for classes and events --"},{"time":638130,"text":"places where nature and mourning meet."},{"time":642451,"text":"Most importantly,\nthey offer us, once again,"},{"time":645871,"text":"a chance to just decompose\nin a hole in the ground."},{"time":651966,"text":"The soil,"},{"time":653379,"text":"let me tell you,"},{"time":655071,"text":"has missed us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657155,"text":"I think for a lot of people,"},{"time":659211,"text":"they're starting to get the sense"},{"time":660832,"text":"that our current funeral industry\nisn't really working for them."},{"time":666298,"text":"For many of us,"},{"time":667512,"text":"being sanitized and beautified\njust doesn't reflect us."},{"time":671947,"text":"It doesn't reflect\nwhat we stood for during our lives."},{"time":676014,"text":"Will changing the way we bury our dead\nsolve climate change?"},{"time":680449,"text":"No."},{"time":682052,"text":"But it will make bold moves"},{"time":684101,"text":"in how we see ourselves\nas citizens of this planet."},{"time":688654,"text":"If we can die in a way\nthat is more humble and self-aware,"},{"time":693286,"text":"I believe that we stand a chance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696232,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697500,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}